Italy’s FTSE MIB Benchmark Index Falls as Much as 6.2%, Most in 15 Months

-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 
2011-08-10T14:36:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/italy-s-ftse-mib-benchmark-index-falls-as-much-as-6-2-most-in-15-months.html
Italy’s FTSE MIB benchmark index
fell as much as 6.2 percent in Milan, the most since May 2010,
led by Intesa Sanpaolo SpA and  UniCredit SpA (UCG) , the country’s two
largest banks.  The index declined 884.97, or 5.6 percent, to 14,836.48 at
4:29 p.m. in Milan. Intesa Sanpaolo dropped 14.3 cents, or 11
percent, to 1.17 euros, after being suspended for at least the
fifth time. UniCredit SpA fell 8.4 cents, or 7.9 percent, to
98.3 cents.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Bertacche at 
 mbertacche@bloomberg.net  